{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","data":{"coaching":[{"coaching":"Pin down the signed LINK event uuid substitution command with a concrete worked example.","decision":"block","finding_refs":["f3b0873b9f1f93b17","f56a6d5c764487a77"],"move_id":"6","move_name":"specification by example","subject":"the signed LINK event uuid substitution command"},{"coaching":"Plan how aggregate-field versus event-specific signature proof will be verified in-session — restate any deferred or unobservable success target as an observable proxy.","decision":"block","finding_refs":["fd2129d957af1e94c"],"move_id":"9","move_name":"plan the verification","subject":"aggregate-field versus event-specific signature proof"},{"coaching":"State the concrete attestation evidence the [operator-attested] container inspection as fallback versus substitute evidence will require (a change id / vote outcome / timestamp), recorded on the ticket.","decision":"advisory","finding_refs":["f1bd7d4a3584ddbc9","f9fd8492c15250660"],"move_id":"14","move_name":"state attestation evidence","subject":"container inspection as fallback versus substitute evidence"},{"coaching":"Plan how the stale inline comment at fetch-secrets.sh:97 will be verified in-session — restate any deferred or unobservable success target as an observable proxy.","decision":"advisory","finding_refs":["fe0bef2ef9a526779","f9896b780b3a700f7"],"move_id":"9","move_name":"plan the verification","subject":"the stale inline comment at fetch-secrets.sh:97"},{"coaching":"Plan how acceptance-criteria completeness and definition of done will be verified in-session — restate any deferred or unobservable success target as an observable proxy.","decision":"advisory","finding_refs":["f607dd457c67f9209"],"move_id":"9","move_name":"plan the verification","subject":"acceptance-criteria completeness and definition of done"}],"coverage":{"counts":{"advisory_overflow":0,"advisory_surfaced":5,"blocking":2,"dropped":6,"indeterminate":0},"det":{"P1":{"ac_items":4,"blocking":false,"clarity_score":7,"name":"readiness-shape","ran":true,"status":"pass"},"P2":{"blocking":false,"name":"resolution","ran":true,"references":0,"resolved":0,"status":"pass"},"P3":{"blocking":false,"name":"package-existence","packages":0,"ran":true,"status":"pass"},"P4":{"ac_items":4,"blocking":false,"desc_chars":5706,"file_impact":0,"name":"oversize","ran":true,"status":"pass"},"P5":{"blocking":false,"children":0,"name":"task-dag","ran":true,"status":"pass"},"P6":{"ac_items":4,"blocking":false,"name":"ac-quality","ran":true,"status":"fail","verify_commands_linted":57,"verify_lint_abstained":56},"P7":{"blocking":false,"destructive_hits":[],"name":"destructive-sniff","ran":true,"status":"pass"},"P8":{"blocking":false,"budget_tokens":868000,"name":"reviewability","plan_tokens":1448,"ran":true,"status":"pass"},"P9":{"applicable":true,"blocking":false,"file_impact":0,"name":"file-impact-coverage","ran":true,"status":"fail"}},"floored_criteria":["A1","G6"],"floored_finding_ids":["fe0bef2ef9a526779","f9896b780b3a700f7"],"llm_ran":true,"metrics":{"claim_path":"no-llm/no-network (structural; the fast claim check is a local HMAC verify)","det_ms":208.8,"llm_calls":30,"llm_ms":379548.6,"total_ms":379885.5,"verify_requests":9},"narrowed":true,"remediation":{"baseline":"sidecar","eligible":true,"reasons":{"code_unchanged":true,"plan_changed":true,"registry_unchanged":true,"sidecar_baseline":true,"within_window":true}},"routing":{"agent_tier":["A1","E4","G1G2","G6","G7","T1","T10","T11","T13","T14","T3","T5c","T8","removal-rationale"],"single_turn":["COH","E1","E2","E3","E5","E6","F1","G5","T12","T2","T4","T5b","T5d","T5e","T6","T7","T9","hedge"]}},"findings":[{"block_threshold":0.6,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Replace or supplement the aggregate `.authorship.signed >= 1` check with a command that asserts the specific LINK event `E` is signed, e.g. `rebar show <t> | jq --arg u \"$E\" -e '.events[] | select(.uuid == $u) | .signed == true'` (or equivalent per the schema), so the check is scoped to the bot's event rather than the ticket aggregate.","cohort":["E2","E6","F1"],"criteria":["E6","F1"],"decision":"block","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["Plan states the check proves 'signature present on the LINK-target ticket' but `.authorship.signed` is described as an aggregate count","A real work ticket 't' is used (not guaranteed to be event-empty before the canary run), so pre-existing signed events could satisfy the aggregate threshold independently of the bot LINK"],"finding":"The first half of AC2's proving command (`rebar show <t> | jq -e '.authorship.signed >= 1'`) checks an aggregate field on the work ticket, not the specific LINK event written by the review-bot. If the work ticket already has one or more signed events from other authors, this check passes even if the bot's reciprocal LINK event is unsigned, giving a false-green result for the criterion 'signature present on the LINK-target ticket'.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"fd2129d957af1e94c","impact":0.85,"is_primary":null,"location":"AC2: `rebar show <t> | jq -e '.authorship.signed >= 1'`","norm_id":"n42561480543d135e","priority":0.7438,"reason":"high-priority+criterion-opted-in","scenarios":["Canary is run against an existing work ticket that already has signed events; the bot LINK is emitted unsigned due to a key-load bug; `.authorship.signed >= 1` is still ≥1 from prior events; AC2 passes; the bug goes undetected"],"severity":"critical","suggested_fix":"Replace:\n```\nrebar show <t> | jq -e '.authorship.signed >= 1'\n```\nWith (after `export E=<uuid>`):\n```\nrebar show <t> | jq --arg u \"$E\" -e '.events[] | select(.uuid == $u) | .signed == true'\n```\nThis isolates the signature assertion to the bot's specific LINK event.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.875,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"na","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"no","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"yes","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"yes","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"yes"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"underspecified_oracle","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"low","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"medium","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"silent","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.7,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Fix the shell-expansion defect in the AC2 (and AC4) proving command: add a setup step `E=<recorded-uuid>` and quote the variable in the jq invocation — `rebar verify-identity --all --format json | jq --arg u \"$E\" -e 'all(.[]; .event_uuid != $u)'` — so jq receives the actual uuid string, not the literal character 'E'.","cohort":["T8"],"criteria":["T8"],"decision":"block","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["Plan AC2 writes: `rebar verify-identity --all --format json | jq --arg u E -e 'all(.[]; .event_uuid != $u)'` where E is described as 'the event uuid' but is never assigned as a shell variable before the command","jq manual: `--arg name value` sets `$name` to the literal string `value`; here `value` is the bare token `E`, so `$u` receives the 4-character string 'E', not the uuid","No `export E=<uuid>` or equivalent setup step appears anywhere in the plan before this command","AC4 repeats the same absence-based check by reference: 'absent from the non-verified report per AC2'"],"finding":"The AC2 (and AC4) proving command `jq --arg u E -e 'all(.[]; .event_uuid != $u)'` contains a structural defect: `--arg u E` passes the *literal string* \"E\" as jq's `$u` variable (jq's `--arg name value` syntax), not the shell variable expansion of `E`. An operator copying this verbatim will always get exit 0 — the filter trivially passes because no real event uuid equals the literal character 'E' — producing a false-green verification regardless of whether the LINK event actually appears in the non-verified report.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f3b0873b9f1f93b17","impact":1.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"AC2 proving command: `rebar verify-identity --all --format json | jq --arg u E -e 'all(.[]; .event_uuid != $u)'`; also repeated in AC4 operator-attested block","norm_id":"n6fcc7a16314d1301","priority":1.0,"reason":"high-priority+criterion-opted-in","scenarios":["Operator records event uuid as e.g. 'a1b2c3d4-...' and then runs the command verbatim; jq checks all(event_uuid != 'E') which is always true; command exits 0 even if the LINK event is present in the non-verified report","The signed-event verification step — the only in-session proof the LINK event actually verifies — becomes a vacuous tautology that cannot detect a signing malfunction"],"severity":"critical","suggested_fix":"Replace the bare `E` in the jq call with a quoted shell expansion. Full corrected sequence for AC2:\n```sh\nE=<uuid recorded from the LINK event above>\nrebar verify-identity --all --format json \\\n  | jq --arg u \"$E\" -e 'all(.[]; .event_uuid != $u)'\n```\nThe double-quoted `\"$E\"` causes the shell to expand the variable before passing its value to jq as the `--arg` literal.","tier":"LLM","validity":1.0,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"na","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"no","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"yes","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"yes","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"yes","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"yes"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"broken_oracle","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"high","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"high","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"silent","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Fix the shell-expansion defect in the AC2 proving command: add a setup step `export E=<recorded-uuid>` and change the jq invocation to `rebar verify-identity --all --format json | jq --arg u \"$E\" -e 'all(.[]; .event_uuid != $u)'`.","cohort":["E2","E6","F1"],"criteria":["E6"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["Plan writes `--arg u E` where `E` is the placeholder name for the uuid, not a shell variable; without `$E` or quotes the shell never expands it","Defect taxonomy item #2: shell-expansion leakage — a $VAR inside a pattern must be expanded before the tool runs"],"finding":"The proving command `jq --arg u E -e 'all(.[]; .event_uuid != $u)'` passes the literal four-character string \"E\" to jq — not the shell variable holding the actual event uuid — because `--arg u E` is a positional argument, not a shell expansion. An operator copying the command verbatim will silently test for the absence of the literal string \"E\" from the report, which always passes, producing a false-green result.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f56a6d5c764487a77","impact":1.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"AC2 proving command: `rebar verify-identity --all --format json | jq --arg u E -e 'all(.[]; .event_uuid != $u)'`","norm_id":"n9ac527a94a3c08f8","priority":1.0,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["Operator copies the command literally; jq receives literal 'E'; the filter always passes because no event has uuid='E'; the AC appears green even if the bot's LINK event is in the non-verified report"],"severity":"critical","suggested_fix":"Add before the command: `export E=<uuid recorded above>`, then:\n```\nrebar verify-identity --all --format json \\\n  | jq --arg u \"$E\" -e 'all(.[]; .event_uuid != $u)'\n```\nThe double-quoted `\"$E\"` ensures the shell expands the variable before passing it to jq.","tier":"LLM","validity":1.0,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"na","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"no","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"yes","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"yes","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"yes","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"yes"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"broken_oracle","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"high","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"high","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"silent","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Remove or relabel the 'Fallback: inspect the running review-bot container…' sentence in the 'Confirming canary 1787' section to be consistent with AC4 — replace it with 'Diagnostic only (not a substitute for AC2/AC4): if the signed event is not yet obtainable, inspect the container to confirm key materialization as a pre-condition check, then push a synthetic Gerrit change to obtain the signed event uuid E.'","cohort":["E3","T6","T9"],"criteria":["E3"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["'Fallback: inspect the running review-bot container on the VM via AWS SSM to confirm the key is materialized and REBAR_IDENTITY_SIGNING_KEY is set.'","'A materialized key is NOT sufficient — it does not prove the bot signs, and could mask a signing malfunction. Required evidence recorded on this ticket: the signed LINK event uuid E…'"],"finding":"The 'Confirming canary 1787' section labels a container/SSM key-materialization inspection as a '(Fallback)', implying it is an acceptable alternative when a signed event cannot be obtained — but AC4 explicitly and emphatically prohibits this: 'A materialized key is NOT sufficient… never as a substitute for the signed event.' This internal contradiction means an operator reading the prose section in isolation could act on the wrong fallback.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f1bd7d4a3584ddbc9","impact":0.536,"is_primary":null,"location":"'Confirming canary 1787' section (Fallback sentence) vs. AC4 ('A materialized key is not sufficient — it does not prove the bot signs…')","norm_id":"n434fba5a40fd95e6","priority":0.402,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["An operator under time pressure reads the 'Confirming canary 1787' section, hits a snag getting a real Gerrit change through, uses the SSM key-materialization check as the fallback, and marks the canary complete without a signed event — a false close."],"severity":"major","suggested_fix":"Replace the Fallback sentence with: 'Pre-condition diagnostic (not a canary substitute): if no signed event is yet available, `aws ssm start-session … docker exec … env | grep REBAR_IDENTITY_SIGNING_KEY` confirms the key is loaded; then push a synthetic Gerrit change (see AC4) to obtain the required signed event uuid E.'","tier":"LLM","validity":0.75,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"na","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"no","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"yes","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"yes"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"medium","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"medium","prod_impact":"low","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"self_revealing","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":null,"blocking_enabled":null,"checklist_item":"","cohort":null,"criteria":["P6"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["vague/subjective terms present: sufficient","verify command `aws ssm start-session … docker exec … env | grep REBAR_IDENTITY_SIGNING_KEY` greps the unanchored word 'REBAR_IDENTITY_SIGNING_KEY' — it substring-matches (e.g. 'review_REBAR_IDENTITY_SIGNING_KEY'); anchor it (\\b, ^$, or a quoted key like '\"REBAR_IDENTITY_SIGNING_KEY\":')"],"finding":"Acceptance-criteria / definition-of-done quality issues.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f607dd457c67f9209","impact":0.4,"is_primary":null,"location":"","norm_id":"ned06ebc801a522e3","priority":0.4,"reason":null,"scenarios":[],"severity":"minor","suggested_fix":"Split compound criteria, replace subjective terms with observable outcomes, and state how each is verified.","tier":"DET","validity":1.0,"verification":null},{"block_threshold":null,"blocking_enabled":null,"checklist_item":"","cohort":null,"criteria":["P9"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["file_impact is empty"],"finding":"No file_impact declared on a leaf work ticket.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f2b56a0701da43def","impact":0.4,"is_primary":null,"location":"","norm_id":"n6324407e6516f811","priority":0.4,"reason":null,"scenarios":[],"severity":"minor","suggested_fix":"Record the {path, reason} files this work will touch (e.g. via set_file_impact) so the attestation is scoped to them.","tier":"DET","validity":1.0,"verification":null},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"","cohort":null,"criteria":["E3"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":[],"finding":"The fallback verification path ('inspect the running review-bot container on the VM via AWS SSM to confirm the key is materialized and REBAR_IDENTITY_SIGNING_KEY is set') does not satisfy the AC that requires a signed, verified event — key presence proves readiness but not actual signing. The AC as written requires the LINK event to verify, but the fallback only checks environment state.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f9fd8492c15250660","impact":0.536,"is_primary":null,"location":"## Confirming canary 1787 / AC bullet 2 / AC bullet 4 [operator-attested]","norm_id":"n00d15cdcf1f04412","priority":0.335,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":[],"severity":"major","suggested_fix":"Replace the AC4 parenthetical with: 'If no natural Gerrit change is available, push a synthetic test change to obtain a LINK event and record its uuid E; key-inspection alone is not sufficient to close this canary.'","tier":"LLM","validity":0.625,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"na","cited_reference_accurate":"na","claims_absence":"no","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"yes"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"none","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"medium","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"medium","prod_impact":"low","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"self_revealing","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Specify whether `_seam.append_event` / `rebar.link` is idempotent for duplicate (work_ticket, artifact_id, 'relates_to') writes, and confirm or add a deduplication guard so that concurrent or retried invocations from the live voter and the reconciler do not produce a second LINK event on the same ticket.","cohort":["E3","T6","T9"],"criteria":["T9"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["'Its on-box backfill reconciler (review_bot/reconcile.py:223, launched app.py:101) drives the same voter.'","'graph/_links.py:264-267 writes a reciprocal LINK event into the work-ticket dir → _seam.append_event(work_ticket, \"LINK\", …)'","No mention of deduplication or idempotency guard in _seam.append_event or rebar.link for duplicate invocations on the same (work_ticket, artifact_id) pair."],"finding":"The plan identifies two independent code paths that both invoke the reciprocal `relates_to` LINK write on the same work ticket (the live Gerrit webhook voter path and the on-box backfill reconciler `reconcile.py:223` / `app.py:101`), but does not specify whether `_seam.append_event` (or `rebar.link`) is idempotent — i.e., whether duplicate LINK events can be written if both paths fire for the same change. Under at-least-once delivery or a reconciler race, a duplicate unsigned (or signed) LINK event could be appended, producing a spurious entry in the non-verified report and undermining the canary evidence.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"fb75975ce31ff5fd5","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"What — 'review-bot reciprocal relates_to LINK on the trailer-cited work ticket → IN-SCOPE WRITER'; `voter.py:278`; `reconcile.py:223`; `app.py:101`; `graph/_links.py:264-267`","norm_id":"nb888385d4c209051","priority":0.0,"reason":"low-validity","scenarios":["Reconciler and live webhook both fire for the same Gerrit change; two LINK events are appended — one signed, one possibly not (e.g., if signing key was transiently absent on one invocation); the unsigned duplicate shows up in the non-verified report and invalidates or complicates canary evidence.","Retry after a transient network failure causes double-write; canary uuid recording becomes ambiguous (which event is E?)."],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"In the plan, add a note stating whether `rebar.link` is a no-op if the link already exists (check `graph/_links.py` for an existence check before appending). If no guard exists, scope a one-line fix: before calling `_seam.append_event`, check whether a LINK event with the same `(source, target, type)` tuple already exists in the ticket's event log and skip the write if so.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.25,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"na","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"no","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"no","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"none","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Resolve the G7 conflict: the parent (297d) explicitly declares 'the review-bot writes only exempt types'; the leaf contradicts this by classifying the review-bot's reciprocal `relates_to` LINK as an in-scope writer — update the parent plan to correct the review-bot classification before re-reviewing this leaf, or realign the leaf to treat the review-bot as exempt consistent with the parent.","cohort":["G7"],"criteria":["G7"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["Parent (297d) What item 3 states: 'the review-bot writes only exempt types' — a settled classification that drove the parent's decision NOT to require signing confirmation for the review-bot.","Leaf plan explicitly acknowledges the contradiction: 'This LINK-write path refines the earlier \"review-bot writes only the exempt code_review type\" assessment — the reciprocal relates_to back-link onto the non-exempt work ticket was not accounted for there.'","Under G7, the parent's plan is authoritative; the leaf may not silently override a parent's explicit design claim. If the parent's classification is wrong, the parent must be updated first.","Parent story 297d is already closed with all 7 child tasks enumerated and closed; the leaf is an additional task that extends the parent's scope beyond what the parent declared complete."],"finding":"The leaf contradicts a specific, material design claim in the parent's plan (297d, What item 3): the parent explicitly states 'the review-bot writes only exempt types' and therefore treats the review-bot as not requiring signing confirmation. The leaf reclassifies the review-bot's reciprocal `relates_to` LINK write as an IN-SCOPE WRITER and makes confirming its signing the entire deliverable — a direct contradiction of the parent's settled classification, not a consistent narrowing of it.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f9e3b050fe385cf2c","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"Parent 297d, What item 3: 'AWS review-bot + auto-lander — SSM-stored signing key; the auto-lander comments on work tickets (non-exempt) so it MUST sign; the review-bot writes only exempt types.' vs. leaf section 'What — enumerate and classify every Gerrit-side store operation', bullet 'review-bot reciprocal `relates_to` LINK … → IN-SCOPE WRITER'","norm_id":"n25c4844c9d52e171","priority":0.0,"reason":"low-validity","scenarios":["The parent's AC3 ('each ticket-event-writing environment... produces SIGNED events') was attested with the review-bot classified as exempt — if the leaf's reclassification is correct, the parent's AC3 attestation is materially incomplete, yet the parent is closed and signed.","A reader following the parent plan expects the review-bot to be a non-writer of in-scope events; the leaf delivers the opposite conclusion without the parent being updated to reflect the corrected understanding."],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"Update parent 297d's What item 3 to add: 'Note: the review-bot also emits a reciprocal `relates_to` LINK onto the non-exempt work ticket (voter.py:278 → graph/_links.py:264-267), which IS an in-scope write; the review-bot is therefore also provisioned to sign (fetch-secrets.sh:98-124).' Then re-review the leaf against the corrected parent. Alternatively, if the parent AC3 attestation is already satisfied by the deployed signing provisioning, a brief parent comment acknowledging the classification correction (without reopening) may be acceptable depending on project governance norms.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.4286,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"na","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"no","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"yes","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"na","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.6,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"","cohort":null,"criteria":["G6"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":[],"finding":"AC4's fallback acceptance criterion ('SSM/container inspection showing the materialized key') is a proxy for the actual goal and can mask a genuine signing malfunction — a materialized key does not prove the signing mechanism works end-to-end (identity resolution could fail, key format could be wrong, or the signing code path could be unreachable), so accepting it on equal footing with an actual signed+verified event makes the canary attestation misleadingly weak.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"fa283b2611d020213","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"Acceptance Criteria — AC4 ([operator-attested] Canary 1787), fallback clause: 'or the SSM/container inspection showing the materialized key'","norm_id":"na2bf6eaa5d5a323f","priority":0.0,"reason":"low-validity","scenarios":[],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"Replace 'or the SSM/container inspection...' in AC4 with: 'If no natural Gerrit change is available, trigger one synthetically (e.g., push a no-op change); the SSM/container inspection (key materialized + REBAR_IDENTITY_SIGNING_KEY set) may be used as a *diagnostic aid* but does not satisfy this AC — only a recorded signed+verified event uuid does.'","tier":"LLM","validity":0.375,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"na","cited_reference_accurate":"na","claims_absence":"no","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"none","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"","cohort":null,"criteria":["G7"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":[],"finding":"The leaf reclassifies the review-bot as an IN-SCOPE (non-exempt) writer via its reciprocal `relates_to` LINK, directly contradicting the parent plan (297d What item 3) which states 'the review-bot writes only exempt types.' Per the CONFLICT RULE the parent wins; the leaf may not silently diverge from the parent's classification.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"fb3b162dbe6f46c3c","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"Leaf 'What — enumerate and classify' section (review-bot reciprocal relates_to LINK → IN-SCOPE WRITER) vs. parent 297d What item 3 ('the review-bot writes only exempt types')","norm_id":"n70eebd674f9bc0d6","priority":0.0,"reason":"low-validity","scenarios":[],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"If the review-bot LINK write is genuinely non-exempt (the more likely correct assessment given the code evidence in the leaf), update parent 297d What item 3 to read 'the review-bot writes exempt types (code_review artifacts) AND a non-exempt reciprocal LINK onto work tickets — the LINK write must be confirmed signed' — then re-review 297d's plan before approving this leaf.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.4286,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"na","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"no","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"yes","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"na","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"none","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Add to this story's scope (or record as a comment on the ticket): update `infra/scripts/fetch-secrets.sh:97` to reflect that the bot signing key is required for the IN-SCOPE reciprocal `relates_to` LINK, not merely attribution-only.","cohort":["A1"],"criteria":["A1"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":"novelty","evidence":["fetch-secrets.sh:97: 'the reviewbot writes unsigned (its types are gate-exempt, so this is attribution only)'","Plan 'What' section: 'review-bot reciprocal relates_to LINK on the trailer-cited work ticket → IN-SCOPE WRITER'","Plan 'What' section: 'This LINK-write path refines the earlier \"review-bot writes only the exempt code_review type\" assessment'"],"finding":"The plan's reclassification of the review-bot's reciprocal `relates_to` LINK as IN-SCOPE directly contradicts the inline comment at `fetch-secrets.sh:97` ('its types are gate-exempt, so this is attribution only'), but the plan does not flag this stale comment for correction. Leaving it uncorrected means future operators reading `fetch-secrets.sh` will incorrectly conclude signing is optional for the bot, undermining the value of the classification work this story performs.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"fe0bef2ef9a526779","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"infra/scripts/fetch-secrets.sh:97 / Plan 'What — enumerate and classify' section","norm_id":"ncd6884cd9a921ce5","priority":0.0,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["A future operator reads fetch-secrets.sh:97 and concludes the signing key is optional/attribution-only for the bot, then deprioritizes ensuring the key is materialized — causing unsigned LINK events to appear in the non-verified report under enforcement.","A new infra script or deployment runbook copies the stale comment, propagating the misclassification."],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"Change fetch-secrets.sh:97 from 'its types are gate-exempt, so this is attribution only' to 'the reciprocal relates_to LINK onto the work ticket is IN-SCOPE (non-exempt), so the key is needed for verified authorship, not just attribution'.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.75,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"yes","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"yes"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.6,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Update the comment at `fetch-secrets.sh:97` to reflect that the review-bot's reciprocal `relates_to` LINK onto non-exempt work tickets IS in-scope (not gate-exempt), so an absent signing key produces unsigned in-scope events — not merely 'attribution only'.","cohort":["G6"],"criteria":["G6"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":"novelty","evidence":["fetch-secrets.sh line 97: 'Blank ⇒ the reviewbot writes unsigned (its types are gate-exempt, so this is attribution only)' — written before the plan discovered the reciprocal LINK on the non-exempt work ticket is in-scope.","Plan: 'review-bot reciprocal relates_to LINK on the trailer-cited work ticket → IN-SCOPE WRITER' — this reclassification makes the 'gate-exempt' comment wrong.","_apply_authorship (seam.py:306-312) swallows signing failures silently and writes unsigned — so an absent key produces an unsigned LINK event, not an error.","AC4: 'A materialized key is not sufficient — it does not prove the bot signs' — implies the plan already knows the key can be present-but-non-functional, but the script comment implies the opposite (key absence is benign)."],"finding":"The comment at fetch-secrets.sh:97 ('its types are gate-exempt, so this is attribution only') is now factually incorrect after this plan's reclassification: the reciprocal relates_to LINK written to the non-exempt work ticket IS in-scope. If the SSM param is absent or the key path is empty, the bot signs nothing and the LINK is unsigned — but an operator reading the script comment would conclude this is harmless. This creates a mechanism correctness risk: a future operator running fetch-secrets.sh without the SSM param populated might dismiss the absent key as a non-issue, yet the deployed-VM proof in AC2/AC4 would then fail silently (unsigned event, not in report as verified). The plan's own ACs catch this, but the stale comment is a latent hazard that survives this story.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f9896b780b3a700f7","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"infra/scripts/fetch-secrets.sh:97 / plan section 'Already provisioned to sign'","norm_id":"n9526c7aadffb396a","priority":0.0,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["Future operator re-provisions the VM and sees no rebar-bot-signing-key SSM param; reads the fetch-secrets.sh comment and concludes this is fine ('gate-exempt, attribution only'); proceeds; enforcement flip (8d39) lands; unsigned LINK events now fail the merge gate.","A new developer auditing signing coverage reads the script and incorrectly concludes review-bot writes are fully gate-exempt, missing the in-scope LINK path."],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"Change line 97 to: `# OPTIONAL but recommended: without this key, the review-bot writes its reciprocal relates_to LINKs unsigned. Those LINKs target non-exempt work tickets and ARE in-scope for identity.require_authenticated — unsigned LINKs will fail the merge-gate once enforcement is on (story 8d39).`","tier":"LLM","validity":0.75,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"na","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"no","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"yes","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"yes"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"low","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"silent","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}}],"impact_model_version":"plan-v3","material_fingerprint":"0e5412bf2a3e8f68","metrics":{"claim_path":"no-llm/no-network (structural; the fast claim check is a local HMAC verify)","det_ms":208.8,"llm_calls":30,"llm_ms":379548.6,"total_ms":379885.5,"verify_requests":9},"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","regver":"b293b9a55de591cc","runner":"pydantic_ai","schema":"plan_review_result_v2","ticket_id":"1a51-b170-5168-46d2","ticket_type":"story","verdict":"BLOCK","verified_at_sha":"2165ee5cf60d83451c602a58cc7cd21619cb3b24"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"REVIEW_RESULT","timestamp":1784237022397301001,"uuid":"8ef1239a-5afa-49fc-9865-b1c20b8024b3"}